UCAR ArchivesSpace Public UI Customization Plugin
Overview
This plugin customizes the Public User Interface (PUI) for an ArchivesSpace installation at UCAR. It modifies menu items, applies default configuration settings, and provides hooks for further UI enhancements.

It is designed to:
•	- Add extra navigation items to the Public UI menu.
•	- Set default values for specific ArchivesSpace configuration parameters.
•	- Provide an easy starting point for additional customization (CSS, templates, etc.).
Features
•	- Adds a Home link and a Browse label to the PUI navigation bar.
•	- Sets defaults for:
•	- archives_request_hidden (default: false)
•	- archives_home (default: '/')
•	- Structure supports adding localized text, images, and frontend assets easily.
Directory Structure
plugin_root/
├── public/
│   ├── assets/        # Static assets like CSS, JS, and images
│   ├── controllers/   # (Optional) Public UI controllers
│   ├── locales/       # Language files (e.g., en.yml)
│   ├── views/         # Custom public-facing templates (ERB)
│   └── plugin_init.rb # Initialization script for the public UI
├── migrations/        # (Optional) Database migrations
├── schemas/           # (Optional) JSONModel schema changes
Installation Instructions
•	1. Place this plugin into your ArchivesSpace plugins/ directory.
2. Edit your ArchivesSpace config/config.rb file:

Add the plugin name to your enabled plugins list:

AppConfig[:plugins] << "your_plugin_directory_name"

(Replace your_plugin_directory_name with the actual folder name.)

3. Make sure the following configurations are set:

AppConfig[:archives_request_hidden] = false unless AppConfig.has_key?(:archives_request_hidden)
AppConfig[:archives_home] = '/' unless AppConfig.has_key?(:archives_home)

4. Restart ArchivesSpace:

docker compose down
docker compose up -d --build

or:

docker restart <your_archivesspace_container_name>
Requirements
•	- ArchivesSpace version 3.0 or newer
•	- Docker (optional, but highly recommended)
Future Improvements
•	- Dynamic menu item generation based on repository settings
•	- Improved mobile responsiveness via additional CSS
•	- Enhanced localization/multilingual support
•	- Integration with custom search or browse features
